	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Strandfontein police are appealing for help in tracing three men who allegedly held up a homeowner on Monday 23 January. According to a report from provincial police, a resident was busy in the garden of his home in Cosair Crescent in Strandfontein when he was approached by three men. Police spokesperson, Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana, says they held the resident up by gunpoint and took various items including jewellery, cellphones and cash before fleeing the scene. “No shots were fired and no injuries were reported during the incident.” Anyone who can identify these men is asked to call Detective Sergeant Elton Williams on 021 370 1517 or 083 482 4286.  Suspect 2  Suspect 1     24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.